\sum_{k=0}^{m} \frac{m!(n-k)!}{n!(m-k)!} = \frac{n+1}{n-m+1}
\dfrac{m!}{n!} \sum_{k=0}^m \dfrac{(n-k)!}{(m-k)!} = \dfrac{m!(n-m)!}{n!} \dfrac{(n+1)!}{(n-m+1)! m!} = \dfrac{n+1}{n-m+1}
